import pandas as pd 
 import matplotlib.pyplot as plt 
df = pd.read_excel('table.xlsx', sheet_name='Avg Emp - Creative')
regions = ['North East', 'North West', 'Yorkshire and the Humber', 'East Midlands', 'West Midlands', 'East of England', 'London', 'South East', 'South West', 'England']
subsectors = ['Advertising', 'Architecture']
years = [2005, 2009]
data = []
for region in regions:
    for subsector in subsectors:
        row = df[df['Sub-sector'] == subsector]
        for year in years:
            value = row.loc[row.index[0], f'{region} {year}']
            data.append({'Region': region, 'Sub-sector': subsector, 'Year': year, 'Value': value})
df_plot = pd.DataFrame(data)
df_plot = df_plot[df_plot['Sub-sector'].isin(subsectors)]
df_plot = df_plot.pivot(index='Year', columns='Sub-sector', values='Value')
df_plot = df_plot.reset_index()
df_plot = df_plot.melt(id_vars=['Year'], var_name='Sub-sector', value_name='Value')
df_plot['Year'] = df_plot['Year'].astype(int)
df_plot = df_plot.sort_values(['Year', 'Sub-sector'])
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
for subsector in subsectors:
    subset = df_plot[df_plot['Sub-sector'] == subsector]
    plt.plot(subset['Year'], subset['Value'], marker='o', label=subsector)
plt.title('Trend of Employment in Advertising and Architecture Sub-sectors (2005-2009)')
plt.xlabel('Year')
plt.ylabel('Employment')
plt.legend()
plt.xticks([2005, 2009])
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()
